HEADWORD: deixis
<hw>deixis</hw> <pr>(d⟦imac⟧k"s⟦icr⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Grammar)</fld> <def>the function or operation of a deictic word;
the function of pointing or specifying from the perspective of a
participant in an act of speech or writing; aspects of a communication
whose interpretation depends on knowledge of the context in which the
communication occurs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Deject</ent>⟦br⟧
